         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">14/7/91. ¶  ¶ It is very pleasing, esteemed Doctor, that your monograph of the Characeae of Australia is moving forward so well. ¶  Be so good as to send me  ¶ receipted ¶  bills, according to the for...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">91.07.14a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Otto Nordstedt</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">Handskr. avdl., Universitetsbibliotek, Lund, Sweden.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">14/7/91.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Es ist recht erfreulich, geehrter Herr Doctor, dass Ihre Monographie der Characeen Australiens so gut vorwärts schreitet. Seien Sie so gut, mir </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">quitirte</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> Rechnungen, nach der Form, welche der Rechnungsführer meines Departments beifügt, zu senden, da ich </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">nicht Quitungen über</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> £10 jedesmal an die Schatzkammer der Regierung senden kann. Wenn immer zum Werth von £10 </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">fertig</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> ist, können Sie eine Quitung (nicht blosse Rechnung) ausstellen, wenn auch die Abdrücke noch nicht abgesandt werden können. Ich passe denn solche Quitungen (on the treasury of the Government here), und erhalte nach einigen Tagen das Geld, welches dann durch Post-Order an Lund für Sie dort zahlbar wird als durch meine Post-Order gesandt.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ihre Liste der 1st Decade giebt </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">nur 8 Arten</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> und eine Varietät. Ich muss aber bemerken, dass </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Varietäten nicht</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> als vollzählige Platten </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">aufgenommen</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> werden können, denn wenn Varietäten (ich nahm den Ausdruck “subspecies” nie an. Ich bin kein ächter Darwinianer) als </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">vollgültig</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> aufgenommen würden, dann würde das Buch </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">indefinitive ausgedehnt</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> werden, wofür ich </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">nicht</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> die hinlänglichen Geld-</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Mittel</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> habe. Ich muss daher rathen die var. subebracteata nicht aufzunehmen, und statt dessen eine zweifellos </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">selbstständige</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> Art zu geben. Dann fehlt auch noch </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">ausser der neunten</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> die 10te Species die zehnte Art. Aus Gerechtigkeit zu mir werden Sie gewiss die wenigen Namen neuer Arten, welche </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">ich selbst gegeben</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">, beibehalten.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Sie ehrend der Ihre</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">14/7/91.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is very pleasing, esteemed Doctor, that your monograph of the Characeae of Australia is moving forward so well.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Nordstedt (1891), the only Decade published.</p>
               </note> Be so good as to send me <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">receipted</hi>
               </seg> bills, according to the form that the accountant of my department encloses, because I can <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">not</hi>
               </seg> send <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">receipts over</hi>
               </seg> £10 each time to the treasury of the government. Whenever an amount of £10 is <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">ready</hi>
               </seg>, you can make out a receipt (not merely an account), even if the printings cannot yet be sent off. I shall then pass such receipts (on the treasury of the Government here), and receive the money after a few days, which then becomes payable for you there by postal order at Lund as sent by my postal order.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your list of the first decade gives <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">only eight species</hi>
               </seg> and one variety. However, I must remark that <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">varieties cannot</hi>
               </seg> be <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">accepted</hi>
               </seg> as complete plates, since if varieties (I never accepted the expression "subspecies". I am no genuine Darwinian) were to be accepted as <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">fully valid</hi>
               </seg>, then the book would be <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">indefinitely extended</hi>
               </seg>, for which I do <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">not</hi>
               </seg> have sufficient financial <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">means</hi>
               </seg>. I must therefor advise not to accept the variety <seg style="font-style: italic; ">subebracteata</seg>, and instead of that to give an undoubtedly <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">independent</hi>
               </seg> species.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>As published, plate 9 was described as a subspecies of the species of plate 8, <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Chara leptopitys</seg>. None of the plates were of species named by Braun using M's herbarium names. </p>
               </note> Then on top of that the tenth species <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">besides the ninth</hi>
               </seg> is missing.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Plate 10 was <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Chara scoparia β muelleri</seg>, named by Braun.</p>
               </note> Out of justice to me you will certainly retain the few names of new species that <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">I myself gave</hi>
               </seg>.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Respectfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">Chara leptopitys <seg style="font-style: normal; ">var </seg>subebracteata</p>
         </div>
      </body>
